content.description:
Start on the rightmost side of the sloper rail just around the climbers right corner of the boulder. slap and heel hook your way around the corner. get to the boulder chocked in between the boulder and the wall then huck a great hand jam in between. press and mantel you way up the slopey top out and youre there!

you can also try the alternative top out of throwing for the great ledge on the chockstone, this makes the problem V3+

*The wall behind the boulder is off*
content.location: Located on the same Boulder as sisyphus's sister

content.description: Sit start under the roof on good edges. Heel hooks and crimps bring you over the lip to a thin and/or big move to a jug. There is also a fun traversing extension...hit the lip and keep going right to the juggy arete at the far west end.
Nearly horizontal finger crack roof. Sit start.
content.protection: Low boulder....one pad and a friend to drag it
content.location:
About a half mile up the Jeep road. Walk past the Labyrinth until you reach a big gully/amphitheater feature. Descend.

38°33'58.61"N 109°34'40.20"W

content.description: Invert OW to flared chimney. Sit start at the downhill end using a serendipitous, calcity jug under the roof. Kick your feet up into the crack, then figure out how to take the long way out and up. Best problem at the Labyrinth, if only for how grueling and weird it is. This and Jareth belong to the Kane Creek Invert OW circuit.
content.location: From the rim trail parking, follow the jeep road up the incline for 0.40 miles. When the road makes a hard right, go down and left to the obvious cluster of well-featured kayenta blocks, avoiding that pretty crypto. The Oubliette is in the southeast corner of the cluster of kayenta boulders.

content.description: Sit start on a big slot jug, make a couple moves, grab the codpiece, then crimp to the top.

Stand start in the chimney, flip around to the inverted booty scoot, turn the lip, smile. Sure you can layback it, but where's the fun in that!

This is probably a pretty good start if you're doing the Kane Creek Invert OW circuit.
content.location: At the north end of the Labyrinth

content.description: climb crimps to one of the taller topouts at the Labyrinth
Stand start on nice little pockets, move right to a diagonal rail feature and go straight up to a mail slot jug.
content.location: North end of the Labyrinth, next to Jarreth

content.description: Fun little power problem. Sit start at a nice crimp rail, bust a big move up and right to a finger jug, using poor feet. Crimp to the top.
content.location: North end of the Labyrinth. just past Blond Feather Duster.
